questionsAndAnswers.question: What is human life expectancy in the United States?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: Human life expectancy in the United States is 78 years.

questionsAndAnswers.question: Who was president of the United States in 1955?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: Dwight D. Eisenhower was president of the United States in 1955.

questionsAndAnswers.question: What party did he belong to?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: He belonged to the Republican Party.

questionsAndAnswers.question: Who was president of the United States before George W. Bush?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: Bill Clinton was president of the United States before George W. Bush.
